    "content": "If you can't use JavaScript and your team dislikes PHP, there are still several robust alternatives for developing a web server. Here are some options, depending on your preferences and requirements:\n\n### 1. **Python (Flask, Django, FastAPI)**\n   - **Why?** Python is a versatile language with excellent web frameworks.\n   - **Frameworks:**\n     - **Flask**: Lightweight and flexible, great for small to medium projects.\n     - **Django**: Full-featured, batteries-included framework for larger applications.\n     - **FastAPI**: Modern, high-performance framework for APIs (uses Python 3.7+).\n   - **Example (Flask):**\n     ```python\n     from flask import Flask\n     app = Flask(__name__)\n\n     @app.route('/')\n     def home():\n         return \"Hello, World!\"\n\n     if __name__ == '__main__':\n         app.run()\n     ```\n\n### 2. **Ruby (Ruby on Rails or Sinatra)**\n   - **Why?** Ruby is developer-friendly, and Rails is a powerful framework.\n   - **Frameworks:**\n     - **Ruby on Rails**: Convention over configuration, great for rapid development.\n     - **Sinatra**: Lightweight, like Flask.\n   - **Example (Sinatra):**\n     ```ruby\n     require 'sinatra'\n     get '/' do\n       \"Hello, World!\"\n     end\n     ```\n\n### 3. **Java (Spring Boot, Jakarta EE)**\n   - **Why?** Java is enterprise-grade and highly scalable.\n   - **Frameworks:**\n     - **Spring Boot**: Modern, easy-to-use framework for building web apps.\n     - **Jakarta EE**: Full-stack Java platform for web applications.\n   - **Example (Spring Boot):**\n     ```java\n     @RestController\n     public class HelloController {\n         @GetMapping(\"/\")\n         public String index() {\n             return \"Hello, World!\";\n         }\n     }\n     ```\n\n### 4. **Go (Gin, Echo, Fiber)**\n   - **Why?** Go is fast, simple, and great for high-performance servers.\n   - **Frameworks:**\n     - **Gin**: Lightweight and fast.\n     - **Echo**: Minimalist and extensible.\n     - **Fiber**: Inspired by Express.js (Node.js).\n   - **Example (Gin):**\n     ```go\n     package main\n     import \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n     func main() {\n         r := gin.Default()\n         r.GET(\"/\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n             c.String(200, \"Hello, World!\")\n         })\n         r.Run()\n     }\n     ```\n\n### 5. **C# (.NET Core)**\n   - **Why?** .NET Core is cross-platform and high-performance.\n   - **Example:**\n     ```csharp\n     var builder = WebApplication.Create();\n     builder.MapGet(\"/\", () => \"Hello, World!\");\n     builder.Run();\n     ```\n\n### 6. **Rust (Actix, Rocket, Axum)**\n   - **Why?** Rust is fast, safe, and great for performance-critical apps.\n   - **Frameworks:**\n     - **Actix**: Actor-based framework.\n     - **Rocket**: Easy-to-use, with a focus on developer experience.\n     - **Axum**: Modern, inspired by Elixir's Phoenix.\n   - **Example (Actix):**\n     ```rust\n     use actix_web::{get, App, HttpServer, Responder};\n\n     #[get(\"/\")]\n     async fn hello() -> impl Responder {\n         \"Hello, World!\"\n     }\n\n     #[actix_web::main]\n     async fn main() -> std::io::Result<()> {\n         HttpServer::new(|| App::new().service(hello))\n             .bind(\"127.0.0.1:8080\")?\n             .run()\n             .await\n     }\n     ```\n\n### 7. **Elixir/Phoenix**\n   - **Why?** Elixir runs on the Erlang VM, making it highly scalable and fault-tolerant.\n   - **Example (Phoenix):**\n     ```elixir\n     defmodule MyAppWeb.Router do\n       use MyAppWeb, :router\n       get \"/\", PageController, :index\n     end\n     ```\n\n### 8. **Clojure (Ring, Compojure)**\n   - **Why?** Clojure is a modern Lisp on the JVM, great for functional programming.\n   - **Example (Compojure):**\n     ```clojure\n     (defapp app\n       (routes\n         (GET \"/\" [] \"Hello, World!\")))\n     ```\n\n### 9. **Nim**\n   - **Why?** Nim is a fast, compiled language with Python-like syntax.\n   - **Example:**\n     ```nim\n     import nimbleweb\n     router \"/\": get = \"Hello, World!\"\n     ```\n\n### 10. **Bash (for simple cases)**\n   - **Why?** If you just need a quick HTTP server for testing.\n   - **Example:**\n     ```bash\n     python3 -m http.server 8000  # Even Python can be used for this!\n     ```\n\n### Recommendation:\n- For **quick prototyping**: Flask (Python) or Sinatra (Ruby).\n- For **enterprise-scale**: Spring Boot (Java) or .NET Core (C#).\n- For **high performance**: Go or Rust.\n- For **scalability**: Elixir/Phoenix or Java/Spring Boot.\n\nWould you like a deeper dive into any of these options?"
